The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 The CAB on Wednesday decided to organise residential camps for the under-22, under-19 and under-16 sides before the start of the season in October. While the under-22 camp will be held in Kalyani from September 20, the camps for the under-19 and under-16 squads will be held from October 1 and October 5, respectively.       
	The coaches want to play at least five three-day matches before the start of the season. The focus will be on their fitness, and so we have decided to organise residential camps before the start of the season, CAB joint secretary Biswarup Dey said after a meeting with the newly appointed coaches.       
	While the under-22 side will play the CK Nayudu Trophy from October 12, the under-19 will participate in the Vinoo Mankad Trophy from October 20. The under-16 boys will play the Vijay Hazare Trophy in November.       
	Saikat Mukherjee will assist Tapan Jyoti Banerjee in under-22 cricket, and Gopal Bose and Ajay Verma will coach the under-19 section. Rajib Dutta and Gautam Shome (Jr) have been appointed coaches for the under-16 squads.          
	Former Indian Cricket League (ICL) recruits Deep Dasgupta and Shib Sagar Singh on Wednesday withdrew for East Bengal in the CAB inter-club transfers. Both Deep and Shib were with them efore they joined the rebel league. Ranadeb Bose, Dibyendu Chakraborty, Sayan Sekhar Mondal, Priyankar Mukherjee and Ritam Porel also signed for East Bengal.       
	Avishek Jhunjhunwala, Sayed Eklakh Ahmed, Subhomoy Das, Sanjib Sanyal and Anustup Majumdar signed for Mohun Bagan.           
	 East Bengal beat Manaksia Ltd 4-1 in the Bengal Premier League table tennis championship on Wednesday.           
	 Surkumar Singh, who ended his third stint with East Bengal at the end of last season, Wednesday signed for Mohun Bagan.                 
	SOCCER: IFA Shield - East Bengal vs TFA at Barasat Stadium from 3pm                                                                                                                                                                       
